<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=barn522&Board=monk&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=1Session&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Barnaby (barn522) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Here is a nifty way I have found to raise skills whilst your monk is still fighting. Starting with something like Feign Death (which is notoriously hard to raise) I made a hotkey labeled, funnily enough, "feign". The purpose of this hotkey is to stop attacking.. feign death.. stand and start fighting again (all within a split second). It is surprising how many people do not know how to programm hotkeys but I am assuming you know how to right click and type the necessary commands:<br>
/attack off<br>
/doability feign<br>
/sit off<br>
/attack on<br>
(Easy Huh?! your skill level can be raised this way even while you are fighting)<p>

Hotkeys can make your progression through everquest that much faster.<p>

What I want to know from all the more experienced monks out there... What other commands can I use the /doability hotkey with? I know that /doability ID is "instill doubt"... there are other special moves that I don't know the right words for.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
